Pork and Shrimp Shumai

Filling:
1 lb ground pork
2 oz peeled and deveined shrimp, minced
1/4 c dried shiitake mushrooms, rehydrated and minced
2 tbsp shoyu
1 tbsp oyster sauce
1 tbsp shaoxing cooking wine
1/2 tbsp sesame oil
1/2 tbsp kosher salt
3/4 tsp sugar
1/2 tsp freshly ground white pepper
2 small scallions, trimmed and minced
1" ginger, peeled and minced

In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix until incorporated.


18 round dumpling wrappers
shoyu for serving
chinese hot mustard for serving

For each shumai, spoon 2 tbsp of the filling into the center of the wrapper. Using a butter knife, press the edge of the wrapper in toward the center, Continue this around the circumference of the wrapper, intenting every 1/4". In a steamer set over a pot of wimmering water, steam the dumplings in batches, covered, until cooked through, 10 min. Transfer to a platter and serve with shoyu and mustard on the side.
